==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prow
<hw>Prow</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>proue</ets> (cf.
Sp. & Pg. <ets>proa</ets>, It. <ets>prua</ets>), L. <ets>prora</ets>,
Gr. <?/, akin to <?/ before. See <er>Pro-</er>, and cf.
<er>Prore</er>.]</ety> <def>The fore part of a vessel; the bow; the
stem; hence, the vessel itself.</def> <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The floating vessel swum⟦br⟧
Uplifted, and secure with beaked <qex>prow</qex>⟦br⟧
rode tilting o'er the waves.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prow</ent>⟦br⟧

