==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prow
<hw>Prow</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Prower</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Prowest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>prou</ets>,
<ets>preu</ets>, F. <ets>preux</ets>, fr. L. <ets>pro</ets>,
<ets>prod</ets>, in <ets>prodesse</ets> to be useful. See <er>Pro-</er>,
and cf. <er>Prude</er>.]</ety> <def>Valiant; brave; gallant;
courageous.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>prowest</qex> knight that ever field did fight.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Prow
<hw>Prow</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. & OF. <ets>prou</ets>. See
<er>Prow</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Benefit; profit; good;
